svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 21, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yzx1665703131264.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yzx1665703131264.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yzx1665703131264.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yzx1665703131264\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the topics under the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">API Reference</span> section to understand\n    API functions, JavaScript, Java call-in classes and methods, database connector interface,\n    session management, security driver, and the Uniface components.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"yzx1665703131264__ul_fsv_b3n_xvb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"evi1665702596474.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evi1665702596474.html\" title=\"Unless otherwise indicated, all 3GL functions are available on all platforms.\">APIs: 3GL Functions</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owl1665702532596.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" title=\"The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.\">APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ebt1665702919180.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ebt1665702919180.html\" title=\"Java applications call in to the operations of a Uniface component via the URB. Uniface generates Java classes and methods based on the component’s signature.\">APIs: Java Call-In Classes and Methods</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpf1665702915593.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpf1665702915593.html\" title=\"Use the Database Connector Interface as an API for building custom database connectors.\">APIs: Database Connector Interface</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdc1665702668356.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdc1665702668356.html\" title=\"The session management API provides an interface to the Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) that enables you to change and control the HTTP session. You can invalidate the current session, or create a new session with (or without) the same state information and session attributes.\">APIs: Session Management</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqt1665702677943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqt1665702677943.html\" title=\"Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory.\">APIs: Security Driver</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrr1675954670899.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrr1675954670899.html\" title=\"Uniface component APIs are internal Uniface components that enable users to interact with many third-party applications and standards and to access public Uniface internal data and functionality. They are activated, as any normal component, use the activate ProcScript command to call their operations.\">APIs: Uniface Components</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "API Reference Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 21, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use the topics under the API Reference section to understand API functions, JavaScript, Java call-in classes and methods, database connector interface, session management, security driver, and the Uniface components. APIs: 3GL Functions APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript APIs: Java Call-In Classes and Methods APIs: Database Connector Interface APIs: Session Management APIs: Security Driver APIs: Uniface Components Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}